eligibility_criteria.description:
Minimum age: 40 Years
Maximum age: 40 Years
This trial does not accept healthy volunteers.
Diagnosis of astrocytoma or oligodendroglioma with evidence of non-enhancement on prior MR images
Two separate, laboratory pregnancy tests within 14 days of registration (for women of childbearing potential)
Impaired lung function: O2 saturation 88% or less at rest on room air by Pulse Oximetry
radioimmunotherapy within 3 months prior to study entry
Patient has hypersensitivity to bortezomib, boron or mannitol

Central Nervous System (CNS) Function defined as subjects with a known history of
             seizures must have well-controlled seizures and may not be receiving enzyme-inducing
             anti-convulsants, CNS toxicity <= Grade 2.

Normal creatinine phosphokinase (CPK) defined as not exceeding maximum value listed below :
* Age: 0 to < 4 years; 305 units/L for males and 305 units/L for females
* Age: 4 to < 7 years; 230 units/L for males and 230 units/L for females
* Age: 7 to < 10 years; 365 units/L for males and 365 units/L for females
* Age: 10 to < 12 years; 215 units/L for males and 230 units/L for females
* Age: 12 to < 14 years; 330 units/L for males and 295 units/L for females
* Age: 14 to < 16 years; 335 units/L for males and 240 units/L for females
* Age: 16 to < 19 years; 370 units/L for males and 230 units/L for females
* Age: >= 19 years; 170 units/L for males and 145 units/L for females

interventions.name: Drug, Food, Chemical or Biomedical Material

outcome_measures.analysis_method: Descriptive statistics (summaries, distributions, 95% confidence intervals) will be reported and compared with the two arms in the randomized trial phase. Graphical displays will be used to show distributions (boxplots, density curves).
outcome_measures.measure: Percent of patients receiving first line targeted therapy (Aim I observational phase)

outcome_measures.analysis_method: Progression-free rate at 24 weeks from the Kaplan-Meier curve for time to progression
outcome_measures.time_frame: Measured up to 5 years after the last subject has enrolled in the study.

outcome_measures.analysis_method: Blood was collected on Day 1 pre-infusion, during the safety follow-up for those patients who did not enter the Extension period and 6 months after the last infusion of the  Extension Period if applicable.  Blood was sent to a central laboratory and was tested for anti-obinutuzumab antibodies using a validated enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA). HAHA samples were not collected for participants randomized to the rituximab arm.
outcome_measures.measure: Number of Participants With Human Anti-Human Antibodies (HAHA)
outcome_measures.time_frame: Randomization to Clinical cutoff: 07 March 2013 (Up to 43.2 months)

outcome_measures.analysis_method: The comparison of response rates (proportion of patients with complete and partial response, stable and progressive disease) between treatment groups, will use a chi-square test. The difference in response rates between the groups and the odds ratio (with corresponding 95% confidence intervals) will also be calculated.
